│   │   └── feature_schema.json
│   └── requirements.txt
│
└── README.md
```

---

## How to Run Locally

### 1. Train the model

```bash
cd settlement-ml
python data/generate_data.py
python train.py
```

---

### 2. Start the ML API

```bash
uvicorn app:app --reload
```

Runs at:

```text
http://127.0.0.1:8000
```

---

### 3. Start the frontend

```bash
cd settlement-console
npm install
npm run dev
```

Runs at:

```text
http://localhost:3000
```

---

## Deployment

### ML API (Render)

- Python FastAPI service
- Automatically trains the model during build
- Loads `artifacts/model.joblib` on startup

Health endpoint:

```text
/health
```

Prediction endpoint:

```text
POST /score
```

---

### Frontend (Vercel)

- Next.js application
- Uses environment variable:

```env
ML_BASE_URL=https://<your-render-service>.onrender.com
```

- Authentication via Google OAuth using NextAuth

---

## Example API Response

```json
{
  "riskScore": 7.8,
  "velocity": 4,
  "reasons": [
    { "feature": "amount", "impact": 0.3, "note": "High amount: $920.00" },
    { "feature": "velocity_5m", "impact": 0.28, "note": "4 transactions in last 5 minutes" },
    { "feature": "distance_km", "impact": 0.30, "note": "Far from baseline (~1200 km)" }
  ]
}
```

---

## Limitations

- Trained on synthetic data
- No persistent user identity modeling
- Simplified geographic distance logic
- No deep learning models
- No integration with real banking systems

---

## Future Improvements

- Train using anonymized real transaction data
- Add temporal sequence models (LSTM / Transformers)
- User-specific baseline profiling
- Feature attribution using SHAP
- Model drift detection
- Mobile UI
- Admin dashboard
- Model versioning

---

## Security Notes

- OAuth secrets stored in environment variables
- No sensitive financial data stored
- ML service is stateless
- HTTPS enforced in production

---

## Disclaimer

This project is for educational and demonstration purposes only.

It is not certified for real financial fraud detection and should not be used in production banking systems.

